cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.OCR, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) based object detection model for recognizing and evaluating handwritten Bengali mathematical expressions. This involves tasks such as detecting multiple Bengali digits and operators, locating their positions in the image, constructing numbers from series of digits, and performing mathematical operations on them. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also mentions the use of YOLOv3 algorithm for object detection, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a CNN for feature extraction and classification also falls under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with handwritten character recognition, which is a common task in the sub-category cs.OCR (Optical Character Recognition).
